By taking pre-mask and post-mask viral aerosol samples with the sampling device, the method enables simultaneous measurement of viral aerosol concentration before and after filtration. The percentage efficiency of the test mask was calculated by use of the following formula, where A is the concentration of viral aerosol challenging the mask and B is the concentration of viral aerosol after filtration. Phage f2 aerosol was determined as PFU/m3
